The paper discusses the design and implementation of an automated parking system that uses Visual SLAM pipeline, which is a common technique used in robotics (cs.RO). The system also uses computer vision techniques such as image processing and object detection (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to build a persistent map of the environment (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the system is designed to work in real-world scenarios, which involves control systems and sensors (cs.SY).
